\f2\fs32 \cf6 \strokec6 29 But he wanted to justify himself, so he asked Jesus, \'93And who is my neighbor?\'94
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\'a0\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Believe it or not there are a lot of people who try to justify their lives.\cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 This guy doesn\'92t get it...he has the right theology but the wrong application.\cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Our world is full of those people.\'a0\'a0\cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Justify is another word for excuse\cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1\cf2 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 People have all kinds of excuses as to why they can\'92t serve others\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl432\qc\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \cb5 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl576\qc\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs32 \cf6 \strokec6 30 In reply Jesus said: \'93A man was going down from Jerusalem to Jericho,
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\'a0\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf7 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Road from 
\f4\b Jerusalem to Jericho
\f1\b0 . In the time of Jesus, the road from 
\f4\b Jerusalem to Jericho
\f1\b0  was notorious for its danger and difficulty, and was known as the "Way of Blood" because "of the blood which is often shed there by robbers".\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 It is dangerous and yet people still traveled it at their own peril.\'a0\'a0\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f4\b \cf8 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec8 But more importantly it goes from Blessing to Cursed\cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl1
\f1\b0 \cf7 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 People do this all the time\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl1\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 They leave the city of God and the people of God to go pursue something lower and lesser than what God would have them.\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl1\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 We call this sin and it is what the Gospel frees us from.\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl1\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 As I said earlier...this may be you today...you\'92re walking away from God and you know it.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf7 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 We can go from a city on a hill to a city in the depths of the earth\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl432\qc\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 \cb5 \strokec2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl576\qc\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs32 \cf6 \strokec6 when he was attacked by robbers. They stripped him of his clothes, beat him and went away, leaving him half dead.
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\'a0\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 This is what sin does in our lives.\cb1 \
\ls5\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Strips of our dignity, our compassion, our love, our future, our hope...our lives and it leaves us on the side of the road.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl432\qc\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \cb5 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl576\qc\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs32 \cf6 \strokec6 31 A priest happened to be going down the same road, and when he saw the man, he passed by on the other side.
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The man of God who should be the one who stops and helps does nothing...in fact he goes out of his to avoid him.\'a0\'a0That\'92s important.\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 There are some who will go out of their way to help others but there are also some who will go out of their way to avoid helping others.\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Part of the issue is what happens if the man dies in the process.\'a0\'a0\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Priests were not allowed to touch anything dead and if they did they would become unclean.\'a0\'a0They would become dirty!\cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl1\cf2 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 This involved a 7 day cleansing process\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl1\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 It would be a HUGE hassle if the man died.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl576\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb5 \strokec6 32 So too, a Levite, when he came to the place and saw him, passed by on the other side.
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f2\fs32 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Again, this man isn\'92t a pastor but would have the badge of chosen by God.\'a0\'a0A levite was not only a Jew but a special one who was suppose to care for the spiritual needs of the nation.\'a0\'a0He was suppose to be sensitive what others needed much like the priest...and he goes around the problem.\cb1 \
\ls7\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 We\'92ve seen two people now who would have the Title of Saved but the Service of a Sinner.\'a0\'a0\cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl576\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl1\cf2 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 They have a WWJD bracelet and wear it to church and then tell the other person - \'93I\'92ll pray for you!\'94 when in reality they could do something more but it would be an interruption.\cb1 \
\ls7\ilvl1\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 They have a fish sticker on their car but pass by the family on the side of the road who needs help\cb1 \
\ls7\ilvl1\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 They are the people who show up in churches every weekend but never serve.\'a0\'a0And they are grateful\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl432\qc\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf2 \cb5 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl576\qc\partightenfactor0

